Describe:
1. During [Fortune's Favor], commandants can spend various [R&D Tickets] or [Fortune Pouches] to get [Fortune]. The amount of [Fortune] you can earn is as below (this is the capacity list; for the amount of Fortune you can earn, check your missions for details):

Event Construct R&D Ticket: 18,450 Fortune, costing up to 150,000 R&D Tickets;
Fortune Pouch: 2,260 Fortune, costing a total of 400 Fortune Pouches;
Targeted Weapon R&D Ticket: 2,250 Fortune, costing a total of 22,500 R&D Tickets;
CUB R&D Ticket: 3,480 Fortune, costing a total of 30,000 R&D Tickets;
Basic Construct R&D Ticket: 220 Fortune, costing a total of 5,000 R&D Tickets;

 2. You can spend Fortune to exchange for Bianca: Veritas Special Effect Coating [Spring Huntress] from [Fortune Merchant] (Portrait included) and other numerous rewards;

 3. By earning 2,000 Fortune, you can get Kamui: Tenebrion Special Effect Coating [Tiger Imperium] for free (Portrait included); by earning 8,888 Fortune, you'll additionally get the special Portrait Frame [Tiger Cloud Tail]!

Command Bureau Music Player Instructions:
1. Only Commander-in-Chief and Deputy Commander are authorized to <color=#0E70BD>edit the playlist</color>:
      Tap <color=#0E70BD>Edit</color> to open the editing screen;
      Tap <color=#0E70BD>Pin</color> to put a desired song to the top;
      Tap <color=#0E70BD>Delete</color> to remove songs from the current playlist;
      Tap <color=#0E70BD>Library</color> to open the song library;
      Tap to select your favorite songs and add them to your current playlist.

2. Command Bureau members can select and play a song from the current playlist:
      The playlist will <color=#0E70BD>loop continuously</color> unless otherwise set.
